text: Burnett Creek is a locality in the Scenic Rim Region, Queensland, Australia. It borders New South Wales. ==History== Burnett Creek Provisional School opened on 13 May 1902. On 1 January 1909 it became Burnett Creek State School. It closed on 29 July 1921 due to low student numbers. ==Demographics== Burnett Creek has a population of 11 at the . The locality contains 12 households, in which 75.0% of the population are males and 25.0% of the population are females with a median age of 55, 17 years above the national average. The average weekly household income is $687, $731 below the national average. == References == Category:Scenic Rim Region Category:Localities in Queensland
